		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Bluetooth</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">This article is about the electronic protocol.  For the medieval King of Denmark, see <a href="/wiki/Harald_I_of_Denmark" title="Harald I of Denmark">Harald I of Denmark</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Bluetooth.svg" class="image" title="Bluetooth logo."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/d/da/Bluetooth.svg/300px-Bluetooth.svg.png" width="300" height="73" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Bluetooth.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Bluetooth logo.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Bluetooth</b> is an open <a href="/wiki/Wireless" title="Wireless">wireless</a> protocol for exchanging data over short distances from fixed and mobile devices, creating <a href="/wiki/Personal_area_network" title="Personal area network">personal area networks</a> (PANs). It was originally conceived as a wireless alternative to <a href="/wiki/RS232" title="RS232" class="mw-redirect">RS232</a> data cables. It can connect several devices, overcoming problems of synchronization.</p>
